'''Johnny Corn''' is an [[Irish Americans|Irish-American]] comedian and actor best known for his [[Stand-up comedy|stand up comedy]] and for "Halloween 7 Bloodline" as well as "Doctor By Heart.<ref name=":0" /><ref name="imdb.com">https://www.imdb.com/name/nm7197124/?ref_=fn_al_nm_1</ref> Corn's comedy style is best known for its [[political satire]] and its unique and intellectual comedy style.<ref name=":1" />
== History == Johnny Corn was born John Nalty on April 10, 1969.<ref name="imdb.com"/> He grew up in [[San Jose, California]]. His stage name Johnny Corn was his childhood nickname his sisters gave him which stuck.<ref name=":0" /> He was born the son of historian and University Professor Dr Damon Nalty. He has a background in culinary arts and studied to be a chef only to have comedy win out.<ref name=":0" />
Corn started his comedy career in the late 1980s. Originally his stage name was Pycho Cow which was later changed to Johnny Corn.<ref>https://pro-labs.imdb.com/name/nm7197124?rf=cons_nm_contact&ref_=cons_nm_contact</ref> He has performed internationally and is currently based out of his long time home in [[Campbell, California]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/2017/06/04/local-comedian-brings-chuckles-to-campbell/|title=Local comedian brings chuckles to Campbell|date=2017-06-04|website=The Mercury News|access-date=2017-07-19}}</ref> In addition to stand up, Corn has been in commercials, broadcast radio and several movies including "Doctor By Heart" as well as "Halloween 7 Bloodline" and "Comedy Of The Corn".<ref name=":1">http://www.johnnycorn.net</ref> He is currently in production of the first motion picture written and directed by Corn called "5 Comedians".<ref>http://www.johnnycorn.net/upcoming-shows.html</ref><ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7885892/?ref_=fn_al_tt_1</ref> He is known for many appearances on TV. Most notably on the mock game-show the "DID YOU KNOW SHOW" <ref>http://www.pentv.tv/2016/09/this-week-premiere-of-the-did-you-know-show/</ref>
